\pard\f0\fs28\qc  {\b 171.                 BUTOMACEAE}
\par

\pard\f0\fs24\qc  Edit. E.V. Heywood. 
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28 Perennial aquatic herbs, with creeping rhizome. Leaves basal, alternate, linear, sheathing at the base. Flowers hermaphrodite, in long-pedunculate umbels subtended by an involucre of bracts. Sepals 3, petaloid. Petals 3, slightly larger than the sepals. Stamens 9, with elongated filaments; anthers opening by longitudinal slits. Carpels 6, connate at the base, each with numerous parietal ovules. Fruit a whorl of follicles; seeds without endosperm; embryo straight.
\par

